reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Paste from an easy to order from source
reviews.reviewText: This was exactly what I needed and buying on Amazon is an easy and convenient way to get this product. It has good heat transfer and I use it to mount processors and transistors to heat sync's. The syringe dispenser makes it easy to dispense only what you need while keeping your hands clean. It is great to have on hand for those times when the paste you already have is not quite enough or not easy to apply because of the packaging or the viscosity (dried up).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So, Should We Be Asking...
reviews.reviewText: ... why is this thermal paste so cheap, or should we rather be asking, why is all the other thermal paste so darned high?There are several YTube vids comparing all the thermal pastes, so going into it here would be redundant, and of course everyone, it seems, has their particular favorite that they swear by, and others that they swear at, and comparisons as to temps are dependent on so many factors (ambient temps, correct application of paste, etc) that I'll leave all that to the "experts," and just say that like others have stated, this thermal paste works, works well, and does so at a price that undercuts the competition by so much that it has to raise one's suspicions.So, maybe we should be asking we are all the others SO HIGH and not why is this SO CHEAP?For what it is, what it does, and what it costs: Five StarsI am the Totally Unbiased Reviewer Dude (T.U.R.D.) and that is how I see it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing budget thermal paste for GPU fitment.
reviews.reviewText: I have used many tubes of this paste to do a test fitment on GPU’s I repair. I get a lot of video cards in for repair that the customer changes the pads and uses the wrong size. The GPU die doesn’t make a good connection which causes the GPU’s to overheat and crash. I also use this during repairs to test not just GPU’s but any device that uses thermal paste. I apply the cheap stuff and test. If everything works I take it apart re-clean and apply a quality paste like MX-4 for basic devices and more higher end I use Thermal Grizzly.
